:: dinerWork_event_vinceManagerPcSnoop_personal_diner
<div class="divnobr">
<<set $location = "dinerRubysManagerOffice">>
<<jobEnsureState>>
<<updateCharacterLocations>>

<<set _todayKey = $timeSys.year * 10000 + $timeSys.month * 100 + $timeSys.day>>
<<if ndef $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeDayKey>><<set $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeDayKey = 0>><</if>>
<<if ndef $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeLeftMin>><<set $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeLeftMin = 30>><</if>>
<<if ndef $jobState.vincePcSnoopFolderPaid>><<set $jobState.vincePcSnoopFolderPaid = {}>><</if>>
<<if $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeDayKey != _todayKey>>
    <<set $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeDayKey = _todayKey>>
    <<set $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeLeftMin = 30>>
    <<set $jobState.vincePcSnoopFolderPaid = {}>>
<</if>>

<<set _pcTimePct = Math.floor(($jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeLeftMin / 30) * 100)>>
<<if _pcTimePct < 0>><<set _pcTimePct = 0>><</if>>
<<if _pcTimePct > 100>><<set _pcTimePct = 100>><</if>>

<<narrative "Personal / Diner Records">>
"RD_Q3_Expenses." Monthly reports, supplier invoices, petty cash logs. You open August.
<</narrative>>
<div class="quest-progress-label"><strong>Session time:</strong> <<= $jobState.vincePcSnoopTimeLeftMin>> / 30 min</div>
<div class="quest-progress-track"><div class="quest-progress-fill" style="width: <<= _pcTimePct>>%;"></div></div>

<<narrative>>
Kitchen supplies, cleaning products, laundry — normal stuff. Then further down:
<</narrative>>
<<narrative>>
08/12 — Manager Training / Off-site . $374.00
<</narrative>>
<<narrative>>
08/23 — Client Relations / Dinner . . $178.00
<</narrative>>
<<narrative>>
08/25 — Manager Training / Off-site . $187.00
<</narrative>>
<<narrative>>
09/07 — Client Relations / Dinner . . $203.00
<</narrative>>
<<narrative>>
09/12 — Manager Training / Off-site . $187.00
<</narrative>>

<<dialog "player">>
(Inner voice)
Manager training. August 12th. $374.
<</dialog>>

<<dialog "player">>
(Inner voice)
That's the hotel. He ran it through the diner.
<</dialog>>

<<narrative>>
You check the vendor column. All five entries share the same code — RD-EXP-07. You search it.
<</narrative>>

<<narrative>>
RD-EXP-07 — Metro Facilities Group
<</narrative>>
<<narrative>>
Type: Sole proprietorship
<</narrative>>
<<narrative>>
Contact: V. Ruby
<</narrative>>

<<dialog "player">>
(Inner voice)
V. Ruby.
<</dialog>>

<<narrative>>
You sit with that for a second.
<</narrative>>

<<dialog "player">>
(Inner voice)
He made a company. Billed himself through the diner. Ruby's is paying for the hotels.
<</dialog>>

<<dialog "player">>
(Inner voice)
And no one noticed. Or no one said anything.
<</dialog>>

<div class="location-actions">
<<btn "Back to folders" "dinerWork_event_vinceManagerPcSnoop" "secondary">><</btn>>
</div>
</div>